Furthermore, short-chain fatty acid such as isovaleric, isobutyric, tiglic and acetic acid were also found as substituents in NSEs. The NMR analysis showed δ for the hydrogen atoms on the methyl groups at approximately 0.9 ppm (doublet (d)) for isovaleric acid, approximately 1.2 and 1.3 ppm (d, for both cases) for isobutyric acid, approximately 2.0 ppm (s) for acetic acid and approximately 1.7 and 1.8 ppm (s and broad singlet (brs), respectively) for tiglic acid. The hydrogen atoms on the methylene group for the isovaleric acid showed δ at approximately 2.1 ppm (m). 13 C NMR analysis for the short-chain fatty acid showed δ for the CH 3 group at approximately 18.5 and 19.0 ppm for isobutyric, 22.3 ppm for isovaleric, 20.6 ppm for acetic, and 12.2 and 14.3 for tiglic acid. For latter acid, the quaternary and tertiary carbon atoms on the C = C group are observed at 129 ppm and 140 ppm, respectively (
