For the SEs with phenylpropanoid substituents, the main substituents found in these compounds are p -coumaric, benzoic, ferulic and cinnamic acids. The NMR analysis for the hydrogen atoms on the aromatic ring presents signals in the range of 6.0–9.0 ppm. The 1 H NMR analysis for the p -coumaric acid showed signals of characteristic δ for the p -hydroxyphenyl group at approximately 6.8 ppm (d, 2 H ) and approximately 7.5 ppm (d, 2 H ), and the trans- double-bond signal at 6.4 ppm (d) and 7.7 ppm (d). On the other hand, the hydrogen atoms signal for the –OCH 3 group on the ferulic acid is showed at a δ of 3.9 ppm (s). Also, the hydrogen atoms on the aromatic ring are observed at a δ of 7.5 (d) and 6.8 (d). The methoxy group on the aromatic ring is observed in the 13 C NMR at 56.5 ppm. The NMR analysis for NSEs with benzoic and cinnamic acid as substituents showed the signal of the hydrogen atoms on the aromatic ring at approximately δ 8.1 (d), 7.5 (d) and 7.6 ppm (d) (
